      "writtenOn": "2020-12-08T02:05:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e did you try running this query on real data? my reading of this query is that it is very slow.\n\nI tried this on real data and reading a page is OK (it was ~4s to read 100 rows of data, after adding Tags to test results, it increases to 8.3s).\n\n\u003e I think it can be achieved with UnexpectedTestResults - it can replace the HAVING filter - if it doesn\u0027t join, then it is expected.\n\nIt can replace HAVING, but we still need to GROUP, so I think it wouldn\u0027t help?\n\nActually I tried it with https://paste.googleplex.com/5541692334669824, it tool 11.4s to get a page of data. Or do you mean something else?",
      "parentUuid": "47fde908_1bfffb88",
